The United Kingdom’s (UK) Development Financing Institution (DFI), known as CDC Group Plc, said it may invest up to $1.2bn in Nigeria in post-Brexit drive. CDC Group, which has invested over $400m in Nigeria, committed $25m to the country’s small and medium scale businesses last week, celebrating its 70th year of existence in Nigeria. Currently, the DFI has investments in Jumia, Azura Power, Zenith Bank, Diamond Bank, Afriexim Bank among others. Speaking in an interview with journalist Africa, Nicholas O’Donohoe, said the DFI was willing to invest about £3bn in Africa over the next four years, with over $1bn coming to Nigeria.